# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules
#
# Strip trailing slashes so canonical URLs match across sitemap, <link rel="canonical">,
# and the actual URLs Google indexes.
#
# NOTE on pattern syntax: Cloudflare Pages only supports `*` as a splat at the
# END of a source path. Patterns like `/*/` (wildcard in the middle) are NOT
# reliably supported and previously caused a redirect loop on every blog post.
# Use explicit `:placeholder` rules instead — they match one path segment and
# work per the documented syntax.
# Reference: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/

# Top-level routes
/blog/          /blog           301
/experiments/   /experiments    301
/about/         /about          301
/contact/       /contact        301
/now/           /now            301
/slides/        /slides         301

# Dynamic single-segment routes
/blog/:slug/          /blog/:slug           301
/experiments/:slug/   /experiments/:slug    301
/topics/:slug/        /topics/:slug         301
